The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Leyland, Nissan give birth to triplets
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Leyland, Nissan give birth to triplets
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, May 26: Ashok Leyland and Nissan Motor Co today announced the formation of three joint venture companies for vehicle manufacturing, powertrain manufacturing and technology development.        
	The two companies had entered into an agreement last year to launch light commercial vehicles (LCV) in the country.        
	Total investment in the three companies will be around Rs 2,300 crore ($575 million).         
	According to Ashok Leyland, the entity will have a capacity of 100,000 vehicles in the first phase, to be scaled up subsequently.         
	The plant is expected to start production from 2010-11.        
	Leyland said the three platforms will cover applications up to 7.5 tonnes and one of them is the Nissan Atlas F24 light-duty truck.         
	An all-new engine is being developed for LCV applications as part of the Euro III and Euro IV compliant diesel engines.        
	Of the three JVs, vehicle manufacturing firm Ashok Leyland Nissan Vehicles Pvt Ltd will be owned 51 per cent by Ashok Leyland and 49 per cent by Nissan.         
	Nissan Ashok Leyland Powertrain Pvt Ltd, the powertrain manufacturing company, will be owned 51 per cent by Nissan and the rest by Ashok Leyland.         
	Technology development firm Nissan Ashok Leyland Technologies Pvt Ltd will be a 50:50 venture.                                                                                                                                                                
